        public java.lang.String[] getSmsTypeArgs()
        Returns:
        the arguments used to translate the sms type description. Only the first five elements in the array will be taken into account.

      • getSmsTypeCode

        public java.lang.String getSmsTypeCode()
        Each sms type is identified by a code and has two I18N keys of the form:
        • sms.type.code
        • sms.type.code.description: used in conjunction with getSmsTypeArgs()
        Returns:
        the code used to identify the sms type.

      • getTraceData

        public java.lang.String getTraceData()
        Optional. If the WS client set a trace data it will be copied to the outgoing sms sent by Cyclos.
        It depends on the client side then there is no guarantee of uniqueness between different clients.
